    Urlä¸èƒ½ä¸ºç©ºå­—ç¬¦Urlmust be a valid URL

Notice how "Urlmust" is missing a space in one language.

Seems to be a combination of 2 strings:

    Url can't be blank
    Url must be a valid URL

I can't find exactly those strings but these come close:

    Geo|URL can't be blank
    Geo|URL must be a valid url (ex: https://gitlab.com)

https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/blob/master/ee/app/assets/javascripts/geo_node_form/validations.js#L16-18

```javascript
export const validateUrl = (data) => {
  if (!data) {
    return s__("Geo|URL can't be blank");
  } else if (!isSafeURL(data)) {
    return s__('Geo|URL must be a valid url (ex: https://gitlab.com)');
  }
```

### Summary

We want to add the commit title to the pipeline status in the pipeline editor. The easiest way to do this is if we can return the commit title from graphql using the query we use for the pipeline status, like so:

```
query getPipeline($fullPath: ID!, $sha: String!) {
  project(fullPath: $fullPath) {
    pipeline(sha: $sha) {
      commitTitle
    }
  }
}
```

This is related to the ~frontend issue https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/327196
